Privileged (De)Escalation in Facebook Ads Manager

Within the Facebook Ads manager, there is 4 different roles, analyst, advertiser, admin, and the final one is the Admin that created the ad account(We’ll call him the SUDO-Admin for this situation. All non-sudo-admins within the ad account can remove eachother, but no admin is able to remove the SUDO-Admin. With this vulnerability it allows you to deescalate the privileged of the SUDO-Admin to the role advertiser, or analyst. The impact of this is that users could be able to take over a whole ad account.

Proof of Concept

1) Attacker who has admin in the victims ad manager navigates to the settings page of the account (www.facebook.com/ads/manager/account_settings/information/)
2) Attacker adds another user in the chat to analyst and intercepts the post request sent to ( /v2.10/act_YOURPAGEID/users)
3) Attacker then changes the uid parameter to that of the SUDO-admins id
4) Attacker forwards the request and the SUDO-admin is stripped of his privileges and added as an analyst
